The '''Ibeno Beach''' is one of the beaches on the [[Atlantic Ocean]] along the shorelines of [[Ibeno]]. It is the longest sand beach in West Africa.<Ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.punchng.com/feature/people-places/ibeno-beach-so-white-so-natural/|title=Ibeno Beach: So white, so natural|work=The Punch - Nigeria's Most Widely Read Newspaper|accessdate=7 March 2015}}</ref>
==Location== The beach is located in [[Ibeno]], a local government area of [[Akwa Ibom State]] southeastern, [[Nigeria]]. The title, "Ibeno beach" was coined from its location, "Ibeno".<Ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nigerianbulletin.com/threads/5-beautiful-places-you-should-visit-in-akwa-ibom.106980/|title=5 Beautiful Places You Should Visit In Akwa Ibom|work=Nigerian Bulletin - Trending News & Updates|accessdate=7 March 2015}}</ref> The beach is one of the tourist attractions in Nigeria. On June 2010, there was a report of oil spill on the beach.<Ref>{{cite web|url=http://saharareporters.com/2010/06/24/fresh-oil-spill-exxonmobil’s-qua-iboe-oil-field-ravages-akwa-ibom-coastline|title=Fresh oil spill exxonmobi's qua iboe oil field ravages akwa-ibom. Coastline|work=Sahara Reporters|accessdate=7 March 2015}}</ref>
